列车调度曾经在中央控制室内完成，后来这个控制室升级为运营控制中心(OCC)，坐落于奥克兰的{{tsl|en| Kaiser Center}}。

==== 故障与困境 ====
在地铁开始运营前，[[列车自动控制系统|列车自动控制系统]]就被发现有致命的设计缺陷和操作漏洞。有三位工程师在1969-1971年间发现了这个问题，并提交给了管理局，然而管理局对此不屑一顾，于是他们将情况反馈给了董事会，却只得到了两位成员的支持。<ref name="Jain">{{cite web|url=http://132.236.67.210/engrc350/ingenuity/Jain_A_memo_issue_3.pdf |author=Anubhav Jain |title=Ethics in technical presentations: BART case study |date=2004-05-01 |accessdate=2017-03-15 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070302104209/http://132.236.67.210/engrc350/ingenuity/Jain_A_memo_issue_3.pdf |archivedate=2007-03-02 }}</ref>随后管理层在1972年3月报复性地解雇了这三位工程师。<ref name="Ethics Center">{{cite web |url= http://www.onlineethics.org/Topics/ProfPractice/Exemplars/AwardWinners/BARTcase.aspx |author= Stephen Unger |title= The BART Case |publisher= The Online Ethics Center for engineering and science |date= 2010-04-29 |accessdate= 2017-03-15 |archive-date= 2020-07-28 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200728224138/https://www.onlineethics.org/Topics/ProfPractice/Exemplars/AwardWinners/BARTcase.aspx |dead-url= no }}</ref>[[电气电子工程师学会|IEEE]]在得知此事后，发表了自成立以来的第一份法律文书，以支持三人的主张。<!-- 原文：The IEEE later filed the first amicus curiae brief in its history to support the engineers. Amicus curiae直译是“法院之友”，我不知道怎么翻译最合适…… --><ref name="Ethics Center"/>美国国家专业工程师协会加州分会在1972年6月也向[[加利福尼亞州議會|加州参议会]]提交了报告，指出了控制系统里有多个严重的漏洞。<ref name="Ethics Center"/>立法分析师<!--原文：legislative analyst-->{{tsl|en|A. Alan Post}}立刻展开调查<ref name="Ethics Center"/><ref name="Dr. Wattenburg2">{{cite web |url= http://www.pushback.com/Wattenburg/bio/BART.html |author= Peter Sheerin |title= Bill Wattenburg’s Background: BART—Bay Area Rapid Transit System |date= 1990-10-01 |accessdate= 2017-03-15 |archive-date= 2020-11-08 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201108160308/http://www.pushback.com/Wattenburg/bio/BART.html |dead-url= no }}</ref>，并邀请了加州大学伯克利分校的{{tsl|en|Bill Wattenburg|比尔·瓦腾伯格}}教授担任顾问。<ref name="Dr. Wattenburg3">{{cite web | url = http://www.wattenburg.us/12-01-72,%20MAIN%20Testimony%20on%20BART,%20WHW%20pg1-12%20%281%29.pdf | author = Dr. W.H. Wattenburg | title = The BART Train Control Game | date = 1972-12-01 | accessdate = 2017-03-15 | archive-date = 2020-10-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201023221041/http://www.wattenburg.us/12-01-72,%20MAIN%20Testimony%20on%20BART,%20WHW%20pg1-12%20%281%29.pdf | dead-url = yes }}</ref>

这些漏洞在随后的一场事故中得到了体现。

* 1972年10月2日，地铁刚开通了不到1个月，控制系统的失灵导致了一辆列车在抵达当时的终点站{{Translink|en|Fremont station (BART)|费利蒙站}}后，不仅没能安全停下，甚至还冲下高架桥，砸在了地面上，造成4名乘客受伤。<ref name="nytimes Dec19723">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1972/12/10/archives/troubles-beset-transit-system-in-san-francisco-bay-area.html|title=Troubles Beset Transit System in San Francisco Bay Area|accessdate=2017-03-15|date=1972-12-09|archive-date=2020-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820031243/https://www.nytimes.com/1972/12/10/archives/troubles-beset-transit-system-in-san-francisco-bay-area.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nytimes Dec19722">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1972/12/10/archives/troubles-beset-transit-system-in-san-francisco-bay-area.html|title=Troubles Beset Transit System in San Francisco Bay Area|accessdate=2017-03-15|date=1972-12-09|archive-date=2020-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820031243/https://www.nytimes.com/1972/12/10/archives/troubles-beset-transit-system-in-san-francisco-bay-area.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="KPFA documentary">{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/pra-BC1167|title=What is BART, and why are we saying such terrible things about it?|accessdate=2017-03-15|author=Bill Northwood|date=1972-11-29|publisher=KPFA Pacifica Radio|page=2 min : 00 sec}}</ref><ref name="nytimes Dec1972">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1972/12/10/archives/troubles-beset-transit-system-in-san-francisco-bay-area.html|title=Troubles Beset Transit System in San Francisco Bay Area|accessdate=2017-03-15|date=1972-12-09|archive-date=2020-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820031243/https://www.nytimes.com/1972/12/10/archives/troubles-beset-transit-system-in-san-francisco-bay-area.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="KPFA documentary3">{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/pra-BC1167|title=What is BART, and why are we saying such terrible things about it?|accessdate=2017-03-15|author=Bill Northwood|date=1972-11-29|publisher=KPFA Pacifica Radio|page=2 min : 00 sec}}</ref>
{{quotation |列车的运营由管理层监督着：
（湾区捷运总经理）{{tsl|en|B.R. "Bill" Stokes|斯托克}}先生正在位于奥克兰的总部，向参观的交通委员会成员展示这个航天时代的控制系统（于1972年10月2日）。“请看，”他说，“这是前往费利蒙站的列车”。然而屏幕上的亮点在经过车站后却消失了。“我掉进了一个停车场！”驾驶员通过广播喊道。<ref name="Stokes">{{cite web | url = http://www.sfgate.com/bayarea/article/B-R-Stokes-ex-BART-general-manager-dies-4548996.php |title= B.R. Stokes, ex-BART general manager, dies |publisher= San Francisco Chronicle |date= 2013-05-25 | accessdate = 2017-03-15 }}</ref>}}
这场“费利蒙惊魂”引起了全国的关注。<ref name="KPFA documentary"/>[[加利福尼亞州議會|加州参议会]]、{{Tsl|en|California Public Utilities Commission|加州公共设施委员会}}、和[[NTSB|NTSB]]都分别展开了多次调查<ref name="US Congress OTA2">{{cite web|url=https://www.princeton.edu/~ota/disk3/1976/7614/7614.PDF|title=Automatic Train Control in Rail Rapid Transit|accessdate=2017-03-15|date=1976-05-01|publisher=United States Congress Office of Technology Assessment|pages=45–49|quote=Investigations of BART were undertaken by the California Senate, the California Legislative Analyst, the California Public Utilities Commission, and the National Transportation Safety Board. The cause of the accident was traced to a faulty crystal oscillator…|archive-date=2019-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209235923/https://www.princeton.edu/%7Eota/disk3/1976/7614/7614.PDF|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="US Congress OTA">{{cite web|url=https://www.princeton.edu/~ota/disk3/1976/7614/7614.PDF|title=Automatic Train Control in Rail Rapid Transit|accessdate=2017-03-15|date=1976-05-01|publisher=United States Congress Office of Technology Assessment|pages=45–49|quote=Investigations of BART were undertaken by the California Senate, the California Legislative Analyst, the California Public Utilities Commission, and the National Transportation Safety Board. The cause of the accident was traced to a faulty crystal oscillator…|archive-date=2019-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209235923/https://www.princeton.edu/%7Eota/disk3/1976/7614/7614.PDF|dead-url=no}}</ref>。之后，PUC开始严格监督地铁的运营，并派出州政府的工作组入驻运营中心。<ref name="Dr. Wattenburg2" />Post先生立法分析师在1972年11月发表了第一份报告，对湾区捷运“措辞犀利”地指出，<ref name="KPFA documentary">{{cite web | url = https://archive.org/details/pra-BC1167 |author= Bill Northwood |title= What is BART, and why are we saying such terrible things about it? |publisher= KPFA Pacifica Radio |page= 2 min : 00 sec |date= 1972-11-29 | accessdate = 2017-03-15 }}</ref>当前的控制系统并不可靠、项目也存在管理问题，而且也“缺乏改进措施”。<ref name="nytimes Dec1972">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1972/12/10/archives/troubles-beset-transit-system-in-san-francisco-bay-area.html|title=Troubles Beset Transit System in San Francisco Bay Area|accessdate=2017-03-15|date=1972-12-09}}</ref><ref name="IEEE Spectrum">{{cite web | url = http://spectrum.ieee.org/ns/pdfs/03_73_bart.pdf | title = Bigger bugs in BART? | publisher = IEEE Spectrum Magazine | page = 34 | date = 1973-03-01 | accessdate = 2017-03-15 | archive-date = 2020-12-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201206012735/https://spectrum.ieee.org/ns/pdfs/03_73_bart.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>斯托克先生对报告中的指控表示“不仅很失望，而且完全无法接受”<ref name="KPFA documentary" />，但同时，管理层也认为自动控制系统“不能可靠地侦测行进列车前方静止的列车”，于是自动控制被搁置，改用[[电话电报闭塞|电话闭塞]]。<ref name="nytimes Dec1972" />立法分析师在1974年3月认为湾区地铁“管理层和董事会都缺乏目标和管理”。<ref name="Whitt2014">{{cite book|author=J. Allen Whitt|title=Urban Elites and Mass Transportation: The Dialectics of Power|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-uX_AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA77|date=2014-07-14|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-1-4008-5745-6|pages=77–|access-date=2018-06-12|archive-date=2020-05-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200530185548/https://books.google.com/books?id=-uX_AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA77|dead-url=no}}</ref>州议会在同年也就湾区地铁的财务管理问题举行了为期一个月的听证会。<ref name="Legislative Analyst"/>听证会上，Post先生建议解除总经理的职务<ref name="Legislative Analyst">{{cite web | url = http://lao.ca.gov/lao75 | title = Legislative Analyst’s Office 75th anniversary | publisher = Legislative Analyst's Office (LAO) of the State of California | quote = After the state legislature held a month-long series of hearings on the financial mismanagement at Bay Area Rapid Transit (BART), Alan Post recommended the firing of BART’s general manager. | date = 2013-05-25 | accessdate = 2017-03-15 | archive-date = 2017-03-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170321084018/http://lao.ca.gov/lao75 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，议员们也以冻结对管理局的拨款来施压。<ref name="Stokes2"/>最终总经理于5月被迫辞职<ref name="Stokes2">{{cite web | url = http://www.sfgate.com/bayarea/article/B-R-Stokes-ex-BART-general-manager-dies-4548996.php | title = B.R. Stokes, ex-BART general manager, dies | publisher = San Francisco Chronicle | quote = BART officials had to ask the Legislature for more money... but the price was high. Nearly all of the Bay Area's legislators said they would oppose giving BART money unless Mr. Stokes resigned. He quit May 24, 1974... | date = 2013-05-25 | accessdate = 2017-03-15 | archive-date = 2020-07-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200728223721/https://www.sfgate.com/bayarea/article/B-R-Stokes-ex-BART-general-manager-dies-4548996.php | dead-url = no }}</ref>，几位经理也被撤换。<ref name="Dr. Wattenburg5">{{cite web|url=http://www.pushback.com/Wattenburg/bio/BART.html|title=Bill Wattenburg’s Background: BART—Bay Area Rapid Transit System|accessdate=2017-03-15|author=Peter Sheerin|date=1990-10-01|quote=Wattenburg challenged the credentials of three successive chief engineers at BART. All of them left or were fired.|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108160308/http://www.pushback.com/Wattenburg/bio/BART.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="IEEE Spectrum23">{{cite web|url=http://spectrum.ieee.org/ns/pdfs/03_73_bart.pdf|title=Bigger bugs in BART?|accessdate=2017-03-15|date=1973-03-01|publisher=IEEE Spectrum Magazine|quote=David Hammond, BARTD’s assistant general manager submitted his resignation…|page=36|archive-date=2020-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206012735/https://spectrum.ieee.org/ns/pdfs/03_73_bart.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>州议员接着撤换了之前指派的所有董事会成员，<ref name="Commonwealth Club">{{cite web | url = https://archive.org/details/csth_000013 |author= Bill Wattenburg |title= BART: Countdown to San Francisco |publisher= Commonwealth Club of California |page= 28 min : 30 sec |date= 1974-02-15 | accessdate = 2017-03-15 }}</ref>并改以投票选出新的董事会。<ref name="bart_history">{{cite web |url= https://www.bart.gov/sites/default/files/docs/PosterTimeline_v2.pdf |title= BART historical timeline |publisher= BART |accessdate= 2017-03-15 |quote= November 5, 1974, Nine-member Board of Directors elected to replace 12-member appointed board. |archive-date= 2021-03-08 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210308141908/https://www.bart.gov/sites/default/files/docs/PosterTimeline_v2.pdf |dead-url= no }}</ref>调度问题和管理层变动使旧金山的区间延迟到了1974年才开通。<ref name="nytimes Dec1972"/><ref name="bart_history"/>1978年，被解雇的三位工程师得到了IEEE道德上的嘉奖。<ref name="#1">{{cite web|last=Unger|first=Stephen|title=September 1973 Newsletter|url=http://www.onlineethics.org/Topics/ProfPractice/Exemplars/AwardWinners/BARTcase.aspx|work=IEEE Committee on Social Implications of Technology (CSIT)|publisher=IEEE|accessdate=2014-02-13|archive-date=2020-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200728224138/https://www.onlineethics.org/Topics/ProfPractice/Exemplars/AwardWinners/BARTcase.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>这场事件后来成为了工程师职业道德课程的案例之一。<ref name="#1"/>

* 1979年1月，一輛正在通過過海灣隧道的電車發生電氣火災，造成一名消防隊員死亡，捷運系統因此暫停服務兩月。比起現在，當時的電車更容易燃燒；從此事件起，灣區捷運定期舉行消防演習，電車內座椅並改用耐燃燒的材質。

=== 1989年地震 ===
1989年10月17日，旧金山南部、[[聖塔克魯茲_(加利福尼亞州)|聖塔克魯茲]]附近的{{link-en|洛馬普里塔|Loma Prieta|洛馬普里塔峰}}地下[[1989年洛馬普里塔地震|发生地震]]，造成舊金山的多數高速公路嚴重受損，而灣區捷運系統具有防震的設計；地震後六個小時，灣區捷運的列車開始恢復營運，次日凌晨5点便恢复了正常时刻表<ref>{{cite book|title=BART : the dramatic history of the Bay Area Rapid Transit system|url=https://archive.org/details/bartdramatichist0000heal|last=Healy|first=Michael|publisher=Heyday|year=2016|isbn=9781597143707|location=Berkeley, California}}</ref>，成為舊金山灣區內唯一可以跨越多數地區的運輸系統。虽然在後續的餘震-{}-中，營運仍然需要暫停數小時，直到以人力確認所有軌道及各隧道的狀況後，才能恢復營運，但地铁依然保持着24小时的服务到同年12月3日。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bart.gov/marketing/25-years-after-Loma-Prieta-quake|title=25 years after Loma Prieta quake: BART, then a lifeline, now stronger than ever.|accessdate=2014-10-03|publisher=BART|archive-date=2018-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612144935/http://www.bart.gov/marketing/25-years-after-Loma-Prieta-quake|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfmuseum.net/alm/quakes3.html#1989|title=San Francisco Earthquake History 1915–1989|accessdate=2014-10-03|publisher=The Museum of the City of San Francisco|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304002551/http://www.sfmuseum.net/alm/quakes3.html|archivedate=2016-03-04|deadurl=yes}}</ref>

=== 延长至[[旧金山国际机场|旧金山机场]] ===
[[File:SFO_BART_plaque_1.JPG|链接=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:SFO_BART_plaque_1.JPG]]

早在1984年，向旧金山南部延长的计划就已经在研究中了，第一步就是戴利城的[[袋狀軌|袋狀軌]]工程，基于这个结构，线路在后来延申至[[三藩市國際機場站|旧金山机场站]]。<ref>C. M. Hogan, Kay Wilson, M. Papineau et al., Environmental Impact Statement for the BART Daly City Tailtrack Project, Earth Metrics, published by the U.S Urban Mass Transit Administration and the Bay Area Rapid Transit District 1984</ref> 在一度退出灣區捷運系統的聖馬刁縣願意以“购入”的方式（而不是正式加入）提供2億美金（考虑通胀后的{{Format price|{{Inflation|US|200000000|1995}}}}美元）後，系統延伸到舊金山灣區的東邊的構想出現契機。

北康科德延伸線共分兩階段開通，先於1995年12月16日通至[[北康科德／馬丁尼茲站|北康科德／馬丁尼茲站]]，一年後的1996年12月7日，全線通至[[匹茲堡/灣角站|匹茲堡/灣角站]]。[[戴利市站|戴利市站]]至[[科尔馬站（BART）|科尔馬站]]路段於1996年2月24日通車。1997年3月10日，從[[卡斯楚谷站|卡斯楚谷站]]至[[都柏林/普萊森頓站|都柏林/普萊森頓站]]的延伸線通車<ref name="openedsince80">[http://www.publictransit.us/ptlibrary/specialreports/Railopenings.pdf 1980年後通車的美國城市軌道運輸系統] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051111232334/http://www.publictransit.us/ptlibrary/specialreports/Railopenings.pdf |date=2005-11-11 }} ([[PDF|PDF]])</ref>。

灣區捷運系統的公會曾於1997年罷工六天，造成嚴重的不便；2001年的勞資談判中，工會贏得了分為四年增加24%薪資以及津貼的協議。另一次的罷工威脅發生於2005年7月6日，勞資雙方直到最後幾分鐘才獲得協議。2009年，由於系統即將面臨約三億一千萬美元的虧損，管理當局提出減薪計畫以達成四年內精簡一億美元人事成本的目標，BART第二大工會ATU（Amalgamated Transit Union）為表達不滿（主要是工作時數規定而非薪資），宣佈自同年8月17日零時起發動罷工，雙方在開始前六小時達成初步協議，罷工因而取消，灣區民眾也避免了又一次的交通噩夢<ref name="BART2009strike">{{cite web | language = en | publisher = BART | title = BART and ATU reach tentative agreement on four year contract | url = http://www.bart.gov/news/articles/2009/news20090815.aspx | date = 2009-08-16 | access-date = 2009-08-17 | archive-date = 2020-11-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201125135426/http://www.bart.gov/news/articles/2009/news20090815.aspx | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

